# Portfolio V3 â€” Components & layout

Cross-read [`v3-design-system.mdc`](v3-design-system.mdc) for colors and type. Prefer **Bootstrap grid** + **Tailwind utilities** + **V3 SASS** for anything global or token-heavy.

## Full-page slide shell

- **Architecture**: each section is `position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100vh; height: 100svh`. Sections slide in/out via `transform: translateY(${(index - currentSection) * 100}vh)` applied **per section**, not on a shared track. This avoids vh/svh mismatch issues.
- `.v3-portfolio-root` is `position: fixed; inset: 0; overflow: hidden` â€” the stacking context for all slides.
- Each `.v3-section-slide` includes `padding-top: calc(60px + env(safe-area-inset-top, 0px))` to reserve space below the fixed header.
- Transition per slide: `transform 0.8s cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94)`.
- Define **`SECTIONS_CONFIG` outside the React component** (module-level const) so the array identity does not change every render â€” avoids unnecessary remounts and animation resets.
- Sync URL hash with the active section id (e.g. `#skills`) and listen for `hashchange`.

## Section anatomy (BEM-style classes)

- Outer: `v3-section v3-section--{name}` (full-bleed background).
- Inner: `v3-inner` â€” max-width `1280px`, centered, horizontal padding.
- Title block: `v3-title` (use display font for main heading where appropriate).

## Motion and visibility

- **Do not use `IntersectionObserver`** (including [`src/components/Tracker.js`](src/components/Tracker.js)) for enter animations **inside** the transformed slide track â€” intersection is unreliable with `translateY` parents.
- Use **`@react-spring/web`** `useSpring` + **`useEffect` + `setTimeout`** stagger (e.g. `120 + index * 70` ms per row/card).
- Add animation primitives under V3, e.g. [`src/v3/components/Animations.js`](src/v3/components/Animations.js): `AnimationDown`, `AnimationUp`, `AnimationFade`, `AnimationScale`, `AnimationSlideLeft`. Reuse patterns from [`src/components/Animations.js`](src/components/Animations.js); keep v2 imports unchanged unless migrating.

## Nav dots (section rail)

- Fixed column of `<button type="button">` dots on the right; **`aria-label`** per section (â€śGo to Servicesâ€ť, etc.).
- Active dot uses **`green-accent`** (`#00A862`); inactive dots muted (e.g. semi-transparent white on dark sections).
- Up/down arrows: same accent; do not disable both directions during transition unless you intentionally block input â€” prefer a short **`useRef` lock** instead of disabling UI for long periods.

## Cards

- Surface: white; **`border-radius: 16px`**.
- Shadow: subtle green tint, e.g. `box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(0, 168, 98, 0.12)`.
- Hover: lift `translateY(-6px)` + slightly stronger shadow; **`transition ~0.25s ease`**.

## Buttons

- **Primary:** `green-accent` background, white text, rounded (pill or `8px`+).
- **Ghost:** `1px solid` `green-accent`, transparent background, `green-accent` text on light surfaces.
- **`transition: 0.25s ease`** on color, background, box-shadow, transform.

## Inactive slides (UX + a11y)

- On non-active section wrappers: **`aria-hidden={true}`** and **`pointer-events: none`** so hidden slides are not focusable or clickable.
- Keep **one** `main` landmark and logical heading order inside the active section where possible.

## Accessibility checklist

- Real **`<button type="button">`** for custom controls (dots, arrows, toggles).
- **`alt`** on all meaningful images; decorative images: `alt=""` or `role="presentation"`.
- **Keyboard:** `ArrowDown` / `ArrowUp` (and optionally `PageDown` / `PageUp`, `Home` / `End`) navigate slides when focus is on the document / portfolio root.
- Respect **reduced motion**: `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` â€” shorten or disable transforms.

## State

- Reuse zustand + context patterns from v2 if desired; **`env` should stay `'prod'`** for real copy (no Lorem placeholder branches tied to `NODE_ENV`).
